<L>__{exterior officer compound}
<A>__{haven, whistling softly, crosses to the colored boy who is polishing the last specks of dust off the buggy. it is a beautiful buggy attached to a beautiful horse. haven pauses and gazes at it.}
<C>__{haven}
<D>__{what's this?}
<A>__{the colored boy steps back and admires his work.}
<C>__{colored boy}
<D>__{sumpin', ain't it?}
<C>__{haven}
<D>__{who's it for?}
<C>__{colored boy}
<D>__{miss charlie, mr. haven.}
<C>__{haven}
<D>__{where do you drive her?}
<C>__{colored boy}
<D>__{same places. around the hills, down the river, every afternoon.}
<C>__{haven}
<D>__{i think i will give you this afternoon off.}
<C>__{colored boy}
<D>__{i shouldn't let you do this, suh...}
<P>__{(looking haven over,}
<D>__{especially the}
<P>__{bandaged hands)}
<D>__{but ah am.}
<A>__{haven climbs in the buggy, and the colored boy watches him go.}
